        "content": "<p>Do we have a conversion of discrete rational probabilistic distributions to multisets?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Basic</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Mathlib.Data.Rat.Basic</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span> <span class=\"n\">scoped</span> <span class=\"n\">BigOperators</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">distributionToMultiset</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">D</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nonempty</span> <span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span> <span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">DecidableEq</span> <span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">D</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x_is_distribution</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"bp\">≤</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"bp\">∑</span> <span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">i</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Multiset</span> <span class=\"n\">D</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n  <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
